{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Hybrid: Variables + Targeted Overrides\n      Use CSS custom property swaps for the bulk of theming (backgrounds, text, borders), but write targeted [data-theme=\"light\"] rules for complex components that use hardcoded values (hero overlay, capability cards, globe glow shader).\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Best of both worlds — variables handle 80%, targeted rules handle edge cases\n            Handles hardcoded rgba() values and gradient overlays properly\n            Moderate CSS additions (~80-100 lines)\n            Clean separation between variable-driven and component-specific theming\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Slightly more complex than pure variable swap\n            Need to audit all hardcoded color values","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1774929880412}
